caption: Great ambiance but overpriced for the quality of the food.

Had a nice little solo lunch here today! I love all the flags and Kamala decorations. At noon on a Monday there’s no worry of crazy crowds so I felt safe. The caprese salad was very flavorful and then the lasagna was out of this world! My server was very attentive and friendly. Can’t wait to go back and try other dishes!

Mediocre place, especially for the price paid.  The drinks were expensive but just ok.  The food was overpriced for what was brought to the table.  I NEVER ask for salt, at an Italian restaurant (or any restaurant to be honest) but this is the first time I had to.  Our appetizer and dinner took so long to come out (at least 25/30 minutes for the app and over an hour for dinner).  I just want to point out that our server made sure the food came out hot so it was not the server's fault.  The Wild Boar Pappardelle tasted like they tried combining two different plates.  It honestly just did not taste unified.  It was also very bland.  The Black Gnocchi with lobster cream sauce tasted did not have the slightest taste of lobster to it.  The Tortellini Mignon was just alright.  It did pack more flavor than both the Black Gnocchi and Wild Boar Pappardelle combined.  AJ, our server, was kind and courteous.  He's the only reason why I gave this restaurant a 3 star review.
Delicious Food!

I go to this place from time to time! This is the best place to dine.  I go to this spot at least once a month. The cooking is fantastic, the workers are welcoming and the prices are affordable. I like going in this place to have a tasty dinner.

Had my first visit ever today. I love Italian food & am always looking for new restaurants to try out. I ordered the caprese salad & tortellini mignon, and both tasted delicious. The waiter Quinton was helpful and friendly. Will definitely go back again.

We've been going to Floriana for over years. It is our go-to special occasion restaurant. It's a small, relaxed restaurant where the menus are hand-made and they regularly just keep bringing you delicious food. I trust that everything I will eat there will be carefully prepared and delicious. As such, I can always feel confident trying new items. The bread and cheese are fantastic and come from a common serving table in the middle of the restaurant. It's not cheap, but you pay for consistency and quality. If we haven't seen friends for a while and they're only in town for a short time, we'll take them here. You can enjoy a 2-hour meal that never feels rushed and is full of new incredible dishes to talk about.

Enjoyed the atmosphere at Floriana, perfect for date night or dinner celebrations. The food was great, wonderful blends of flavors and textures all round. Lastly, impeccable service- thank you Marco!!!

Unfortunately, we never tasted the food we ordered so the review is purely based off long wait times for entrees and the cleanliness of the building. Our surprisingly mediocre drinks were served quickly but after 45 minutes of waiting for our entrees, I saw a large rat run across the main dinning room floor. There were several other tables in the restaurant but it was not crowded. The table next to us also saw the rat and both parties mentioned it to the staff. We left the restaurant before receiving our food and the staff waived our bill. I’m sure the food would have been fine, especially for the price per dish, but I have no intention on returning to Floriana or ordering food from them due to rat sighting.

I have been here twice, once with my mother for brunch and once with a girlfriend for drinks and apps. Service is excellent, we were helped by a very charismatic waiter who spoke French. Although there were some hiccups with food delivery, our waiter was very accommodating. However, the food is just ok. I had gnocchi for brunch - very simple with a standard marinara, nothing spectacular. Burrata is made fresh in house but not quite as creamy as I hoped. My friend took a lasagna to go and may have had food poisoning after. Also, although they had mentioned that cocktails and wine are half price on Wednesday, the wine only applies to bottles. I would give it another chance before a final verdict but so far it's just ok in my book.

After moving to the area from Oklahoma City since September I have to say this is the best restaurant I've eaten at in DC. The lasagna, gnocchi, beet salad, bread and Boar Papardelle. I will definitely be back.

Decided to try Floriana for Restaurant week this past weekend. Wait time was ridiculously long for appetizers including just getting bread to chew on before the meal. Our apps arrived about 45 mins after we ordered them..I must say the Black Gnocchi is delicious. However our meals were lacking in flavor and taste. I got the Fazzoletti with Short rib which was mostly just buttery pasta. My friends fillet mignon was cold by the time it got the table and the shrimp and scallop dish was quite tasteless as well. Not sure i would come back here..customer service was decent but food left a lot to be desired  2.19 Update..I was reached out to by Mgmt and compensated for the cost of the meal and offered a chance to return to the restaurant to try again..quite impressed with the prompt response to the issues we faced and look forward to trying Floriana again.

This place was absolutely amazing. We came by on Valentine’s Day and had a great time. The atmosphere was really intimate, the pace was excellent, the food was delicious, and the staff was beyond amazing! From host, to server, to management, everyone was genuinely nice and friendly. Thank you for a fantastic experience!!! 🙏
Get the waiter who speaks 4 languages. He is mad cool!! The owner too is amazing. He keeps you really engaged to the place. The food is amazing!!!
Great food and great service! Highly recommend this cozy little restaurant!

Small restaurant in the heart of DC, great homemade italian food prepared by people that know what they're doing. Take it from someone that was born there. Staff is always friendly, will definitely be coming back!
Food was awesome, the black gnocchi appetizer i could have eaten a large portion of that and been happy. Service was a littke slow but we weren't in a hurry.
Definitely a place worth stopping by, the food is good and well prepared, the prices are convenient and it is always well organized here. Great work.

Floriana has a really nice patio and made an effort to create a cozy covid-proof terrace. I prefer their atmosphere to their food and I would normally rate them four stars, but our recent experience was just terrible. We live around the corner and we’re looking for a nice night out so I picked up the phone and secured a reservation for an outside table at 7pm (I emphasize this to make clear I spoke to an actual person). How disappointing to find out that when we arrived at Floriana a female staff member told us they only had a table for us inside, because they don’t take reservations for outside. Confused I tried to explain I actually spoke to a colleague of her that afternoon who had written down our request and never mentioned this to me. She told us we could wait for a table to open up and then proceeded to seat another couple - who were walk-ups and had arrived just before us - to the last available table outside. After that she just ignored us. We were left standing on the sidewalk in the cold. Nothing was done to try to make up for their mistake or to at least make our wait a little less uncomfortable. Excuses would have been nice, but no. This is not how you treat your guests who make an effort to support your business in the middle of a pandemic. Another staff member walked up to us, and after making his round, told us we would probably have to wait for at least 30 mins for a table to open up. Disappointed we left, and we’re thankfully greeted with open arms at Annabelle.
The best lasagna i have had in life ! Next too my mom's 😊
Ask for Cantin Sauvage...he was a great host!

The restaurant is quite cozy, and the food is marvelous. Be sure to make a reservation though, because this place is always packed! And for good reason! The fish is superb, and the pasta dishes are amazing. A definite must if you like Italian!

I went here last week and had an amazing meal outside. Our waiter, Quentin, really made the experience. The guy knew the menu inside and out and made great food and wine recommendations. I was really impressed with him and could not have enjoyed my gnocchi more!

My girlfriend and I went on our first "official" date there and have gone back every anniversary since and a dozen times in between. The food is always good and so is the service. The only complaint I have is that this past anniversary dinner the cipollini ragu served with the ny strip was kind of cold. Unless they usually serve it that way; in that case please correct me. Other than that everything was great and it has been every time we go.
Staple of 17th street restaurants.  Also one of the best in the area.  Reasonable prices, excellent service, and amazing food. Recommend the smoked salmon Benedict from the brunch menu.
It was extremly delightful. Cozy, and delicious. Perfect environment to have a great night. Also the duck breast, was unbelievably tasty. Wonderful place indeed.
Food was great service was good for brunch. I wish I had tasted the pasta

Beyond Amazing. Floriana was impeccable thanks to Michael our server. We literally walked up with 6 people and it seemed like Micheal already setup a table and accommodated us without reservation. He was wity and insightful and gave us 2 great suggestions which was the Lasagna which tasted like you had a Nona preparing every slice. I thought nothing could beat this until I tasted that french toast. This was THE BEST FRENCH TOAST I HAVE EVER EATEN, the hint of orange in every bite just made a perfect brunch perfect. I also can't forget about bottomless mimosas with fresh OJ tasty and affordable.
Went for brunch on a late Sunday afternoon. Delicious food, quaint place. Staff was very courteous but on the slower side.
Flavorful fare, beautiful home, and friendly service...the gnocchi was perfect and housemade!

Floriana is one of our favorite local places in NW DC. The location is great if you are looking to escape busy areas like 14th Street or the Downtown K/Street crowd. The food is amazing, the service is great, and it has become a staple for my wife and I to bring friends from out of town.

Floriana is one of our favorite local places in NW DC. The location is great if you are looking to escape busy areas like 14th Street or the Downtown K/Street crowd. The food is amazing, the service is great, and it has become a staple for my wife and I to bring friends from out of town.
Food is great. Well thought out and crafted menu. Truly wonderful flavors. Inside has unique and cozy spaces. When that's viable again, can't wait to take advantage.
Loved the food and the vibe was good
Delicious food! Having lived in Naples Italy, I can say the food tasted like real Italian food! Will be there soon!
Excellent service, ditto for the food and wine!

Absolutely one of the best Italian restaurants in the  DC metro area! To add some context to my high rating, I lived in Milan Italy for three years and before living in Italy, I did not really care for Italian cooking. I quickly learned there is a difference between American Italian and true Italian cuisine. I really loved Italian cooking. While Floriana, has placed their own twist on Italian cooking, the flavors were close enough to take me back to Italy.
Great food and great service. The lasagna was delicious!
I went there yesterday. I had the lobster spaghetti and shared the calamari fritti. I was vomiting all night. Other than that it was very good: great service,  tasty food, nice environment.
Food was great as always.
Fantastic Food and service
I've had almost everything on the menu. One of my favorite places to eat in DC. The bread that came with my meal was some of the best bread I have had in a long time!

We came for brunch and the service and food were spectacular.  The staff was very considerate and safe during the covid situation. The lasagna, though normally considered a dinner meal was delicious and worked well for brunch. Likewise, the actual brunch food of prosciutto benedict was perfect. Wrapping up the brunch with a tiramisu split between two people was a great finish to the meal.
The food is very expensive and not worth the price. I would recommend to go to other place to get the same quality of food for half the price.

While visiting DC on a Saturday, we found this place with high ratings online. Nothing prepared us for what we experienced. The service was great and the prices for brunch were amazing. It was a romantic scene with a fireplace and elegant decor. The food was delicious and choices hard to pick from. The cocktails kept flowing.....
Wonderful ambiance, friendly and professional service, and heavenly food, wine, and dessert.  The Mignon tortellini and Tiramisu were amazing! Looking forward to going back during my next DC visit.
Very good food. 4 stars because the tables a little close together, I could hear everything my neighbors were saying. Service was attentive and nice.
Calamari, black gnocchi, lasagna and tiramisu are the items to get
Love this place. Great wine, great pasta, and great dessert! Nom nom nom

(Translated by Google) We had lasagna at lunch. When I told the shop that it was the best lasagna I had eaten, my mother made it better but it was even better. The surface is crisp, the sauce is not too much, and the top vegetables like kaiware also add to the taste. I think that the volume is also satisfactory for those who are asked for a large serving in Japan. It was good that the waiter's sense of distance was not too close and not too far.  (Original) ランチでラザニアを頂きました。私が食べてきたラザニアの中で1番美味しかったです、とお店の方に伝えると自分の母が作るのが美味しいがそれよりも美味しいとのこと。表面がカリッと仕上げられており、ソースもくど過ぎず、1番上のカイワレのような野菜も美味しさを引き立てています。ボリュームも日本で大盛りを頼まれる方でも満足できる量だと思います。ウェイターさんの距離感も近過ぎず遠過ぎずなのが良かったです。
Food and cocktails were exquisite. Amazing Italian food. Get the calamari for an appetizer.
Super service, grea old style Italian food, in a cozy setting.
Savoury Italian food. Nice service. Would recommend you make a reservation.
Wonderful atmosphere,  great customer service, servers were knowledgeable and very attentive.  The food was great.   I had fried brussel sprouts and shrimp and risotto. 😊
Wine bar is full of kitch and great people. Food is amazing.  Lasagna to die for.
The lasagna was on point! Unequivocally delicious!

My grandmother took our family out to dinner here for a nice holiday meal tonight. The food was incredible, some of the best calamari I've ever had. The wait staff was very nice, quick friendly service. However, the manager was horrible. He came up before our food came out to say hello and began telling a story about his wait staff. He mentioned that one of his italian waiters didn't do side tasks and proceeded to say that "I didnt know that all Italians were lazy." My family has Italian heritage and we did not take kindly to his words. My father was turning red in frustration from the incident. We may return for the food but if we see that manager again we will take our business elsewhere.
The food is very delicious. Great unique experience.
Food was exceptional and service extraordinary. I will be back 👍

Food was lovely! We had the fried calamari, the lasagna and the venison pappardelle which were fantastic. The wine list was impressive and even offered a Super Tuscan on the by-the-glass menu which is pretty much unheard of (obviously nothing over the top, but still, a nice touch.) We even had a chance to chat with the manager afterward who was very kind and genuine. The only thing was kept me from giving that last star was the service; it was a busy friday night, but the service was pretty erratic (still not sure which waiter was our waiter, we had three different types of water given to us, other "first world problems" that aren't actual problems in reality at all...) Still, I would highly recommend this place if you're looking for quality italian in DC in an intimate setting. We had a lovely night!
Excellent food and service. General manager was really helpful. Loved it.

We had a lovely dinner here. It feels very independent and love-worn, the service was wonderful - Rishard our waiter was full of passion and knowledge about the menu - we did ask for greens with our mains and that got forgotten but the ambience was good enough to let it slide. It was lovely to see full LGBTQIA+ representation across the staff and it was a memorable evening. We left feeling full and content. Definitely go here and put your money into a gay indie restaurants - screw those chains! X
You know those fancy, elegantly decorated restaurants you see in movies that you wish you could take your date there to impress them? Well, this is it.

Wanted to like this place but experience was disappointing. Some of our friends’ food was forgotten for 15-20 min and came out cold when it was finally served. Nothing taken off the bill but we were given a half sized order of pasta to make up for it but the moment had more than passed. Other dishes served on time were not hot, no one came to get drinks order, no one asked how food was, and had the overall feeling no one is in charge. Two stars for friendly attitude of staff who somehow got away without taking responsibility for the poor food and service.
The service was good,my date was the issue

The staff was great and the atmosphere intimate. But the food was only just fine. Nothing special and certainly not worth the money. The menu looked interesting but the execution was just lacking. Really wanted to love the place because it’s so close, but won’t be going back.
I ate here and the food gave me food poisoning. I was completely out of commission for an entire day.
Great presentation of food. Desert was delicious.
Great outdoor seating section. Amazing services. Great atmosphere. Great selection of wine. Environment was good.
Food was okay.  Service was lacking.
Amazing as always!
Great food and service a little too dark
This is a great restaurant, close to DuPont circle. Food is great, wine wonderful. Great with a group of friends

I had to do a double take as I was walking home!! This place is a hidden gem with a wonderful staff — AJ and Brian! The food was delicious and authentic, and the atmosphere on a nice October evening was the perfect compliment to my wine.  This place is great find and I will definitely return!
Come for the lasagna, the filet, and the intimate romantic ambiance upstairs, stay for the potent Manhattans and killer Italian wine list that Dito maintains in the downstairs bar.
Delicious food in Dupont Circle. Manager was very friendly and attentive.
Great food
Menu was simple but had great variety. Service was good. Atmosphere was nice. Had brunch outside on the patio . Nice experience overall.

10/10, I cannot brag on this place enough! Nestled on a quiet corner, this little gem was the perfect place for my fiance and I. The service was excellent, and after inquiring about our visit, our waiter brought us a decadent complimentary tiramisu and birthday card from the staff. Seated at the windows in the main dining hall, we were able to watch the sun set by candlelight (Very romantic!). We both ordered the lasagna bolognese, which was beyond amazing, and so large we were both able to save half of our portions for dinner the next evening! Floriana made our evening so special, and we will definitely be back for more. Authentic Italian, incredible service, beautiful location- need I say more?
Excellent food and service. The burrata ravioli was particularly wonderful!
Classy

CALAMARI FRITTI | $13 spicy tomato sauce *light crispy batter, perfectly cooked calamari, tomato sauce was lukewarm wish it was piping hot *our server offered salt, pepper and lemons which was great  LASAGNA | $22 beef, béchamel, house made mozzarella *usually my favorite lasagna but this was super disappointing, didn't taste any bechamel, it definitely needed more cheese in the layers, I basically just tasted pasta and some tomato sauce, it was very one note  CABERNET SAUVIGNON, Alkoomi 2016 | $60 Robust and full bodied. All the notes of Western Australia intermingling with black currants, chocolate, blackberries, and spiced deep red fruit notes. *it was a good wine with dinner but was disappointed that there were no fuller bodied bottles of red wine for less than $60  DESSERTS | $10 each I found this to be really steep because I got blueberry pound cake, it didn't even come with ice cream so for $10 for a meager slice it's overpriced and it was just ok  ATMOSPHERE: I think the restaurant should consider more lighting, it was much too dark and not in a romantic way
Very solid upscale Italian in a cozy townhouse. Nothing here will surprise or amaze you, but the execution is extremely competent.
Fantastic. Don't miss out on the lasagna!!!

Went here on a business citytrip with my husband and daughter, and if you are looking for authentic Italian cuisine: Floriana definitely is the place to be! Excellent food and excellent staff. Staff was very nice and the gnocchi with squid ink was amazing!

I lived in Rome for one year so a generally have high expectations about Italian restaurants. I went there for the first time yesterday and I was agreeably surprised. Cute and cost ambiance. Good service. food food. Highly recommend the duck carbonara and the octopus.
Best Filet Mignon! Great service! Gorgeous ambiance. Charming staff. This place is a repeat. I promise that you’ll crave to go repeatedly.
Great ambiance in this neat row house restaurant, not to mention the food is great!
Excelent restaurant.
Our lunch was delicious, so was our wine. Service was excellent! We'll be back.
The food was good, service was okay, our server didn't ask how was our food, do we need anything else, nothing at all.
Bird feather on my fork... That's right so eat inside
Mmmmmmm love the meatballs here!
Will be back, loved the service, food, and chill patio vibe.  Also loved the tiny basement bar!
Italian if you must
Excellent neighborhood spot -- delicious food, friendly service, good people watching. We love coming back year after year.

Food was excellent. I highly recommend this place. Quiet setting and the waiter took our order fast and accurately. I ordered the lasagna and it was perfect. The salad was light and tasty. We had chocolate moose. It was yummy.
Great food and service. Very well cooked pasta and good wine selection.
Excellent food & service!

I came here on a weekend for brunch (I didn't know they had brunch), and I got the gnocchi which was made with yellow tomatoes and mozzarella. I sat outside because the weather was great, and I really enjoyed it. The gnocchi was average; the pieces were too big to soak up the flavor, and the sauce was super light and not very flavorful to begin with. The gnocchi texture was interesting, I think mostly they were just way too big. The plate of food wasn't too big and I felt like I could've eaten more afterward. Service was good, as my water was refilled appropriately and I was asked how my food was (although I was asked too soon, basically after I ate my first gnocchi, I was asked this question). The bill was around $13 post-tax which is not bad at all for Italian food!

Pros: innovative menu, entrees were excellent, good wine, nice atmosphere. Cons; dessert not great (crust on apple crumble too thick/underbaked), service a little slow, brought out one of our apps wrong (caprese instead of bruschetta).  But the pasta was amazing.

I came here for my birthday with my parents. I just found the lovely birthday note the staff gave to me. The service here is amazing. All the staff was extremely friendly and accomodating. Truly the best service I have ever had in DC. The food was also amazing.
Really nice staff and very accommodating. Great food and a great outdoor seating area!
Super cute, authentic place. Very tasty, fine cuisine and great service. Absolutely recommend it to those seeking fine italian cuisine. They also brought me a birthday tiramisu :-)

Floriana has been around for a long time, it's one of the older restaurants in the neighborhood. 17th Street has kind of been eclipsed by 14th Street in the last few years, and I hadn't been to Floriana for several years. The last time, I vaguely remembered it as ok but nothing special. Nothing has really changed. Nothing was bad, but with so many really good places  a few minutes walk away, I can't see why I'd come here again.  There are several fairly traditional pasta dishes, like butternut squash ravioli. But again, nothing special or different enough to tempt me back.  They do have a fair selection of wines, quite a few by the glass. Service was fine, and I don't really have any complaints, but they're simply not up to the nearby competition.
Food and service excellent. Very warm in restaurant and I'm usually cold all the time. Dress accordingly for comfort

Floriana is hands down my number one spot for a romantic intimate dinner. I just went for my birthday, and our server Louis was an absolute dream and left us wanting for nothing. We got complimentary bubbly and a hand written note wishing me a happy birthday from the staff. My fiancé got their signature scallops and shirmp risotto, and I got the lobster gnocchi. Both were 15/10 fantastic dishes. If you are on the fence about this place, drop what you’re doing an make a reservation NOW. You will not regret it.
The Branzino was magnificent! Very professional service and maitre d' attention. Coffee gelato was tasty.
Probably the best ravioli I have ever had and that is saying something as I am Italian. A little expensive but it was delicious. All 6 of us agreed that was fantastic food.

I got some takeout from this place an hour before closing and the food was terrible. I paid $21.00 for what was supposed to be spaghetti and meatballs but got a small mess of lasagna sheets in bland tasteless sauce and 2 dry meatballs that tasted like dog food.

Visited Dc for my cousins Birthday and we wanted some Authentic Italian food. Let me tell you it doesn’t get any better than this place. Food was Exceptional and the service was great! Next time I’m in Dc I’m definitely coming back to this restaurant.
Great service. Everyone at a table of 8 was happy with the food. And unlimited mimosas for $15 during brunch. Such a great deal. And the interior feels like you're in someone's home. Very cute spot.

Nice place. A little loud inside but the food was good. The only thing we would not recommend is the tortellini and the pappardelle. Those 2 dishes the portions where way too small for what you paid for them. Appetizers the gnocchi and mussels where so good. Entrees you have to try the sweet potato gnocchi and the scallops and shrimp risotto.

Always excellent cuisine from a great chef with attentive service, a neighborhood icon that gets better and better. Don't miss Dito's Bar in the lower level, for pre-dinner cocktails or for a nightcap, a unique experience.
Great service and food
Surprisingly good
Really great brunch.  Kudos to Matthew who provided great service for us.  I would definitely be back

We came for lunch to celebrate our anniversary.  We were impressed with the level of service and the quality of the food. The beet salad with goat cheese was incredibly flavorful. The lamb gnocchi was satisfying and delicious. The pasta is made in house to perfection. The tirimisu and chocolate moose are rich without being overly sweet - definitely worth the calories. The service was outstanding. Portions were generous. We will return soon, and will suggest this place to anyone hungry for fine italian food in a relaxed, intimate setting.
An amazing resturaunt. Every course was delicious.  Best italian food in DC.    My wife and I went for our anniversary. The staff went out of their way to make our experience extremely memorable.
Basement bar is one of my fave spots in Washington
The meal was incredible as was the service.
Great service. Cozy restaurant. Excellent service! Lobster gnocchi was great, beet salad to start off was perfect.

You may want to make a reservation at this place. MOST of the tables are for two people, but a few are for 4's and 6's (very few).  The restaurant space is a small row house (narrow and steep staircases). The tables are close in proximity and the lighting is dim. The bar is LIVELY and well-lit and on the basement level.  Went with two childhood friends and we each ordered something different so that we could try each other's meal. We each had a different drink (I had an Impeachment and it was delicious, made with peach schnapps and bourbon). The meal started with sliced crusty bread and pesto (very garlicky and made with basil, as pesto should be). We shared steamed mussels (white wine, garlic, butter, parsley) and calamari fritti  (spicy tomato sauce) as appetizers. Calamari was not too salty and not chewy. The mussels were okay, to me. I think they could use a little "kick" of something.  One friend had the SCALLOP & SHRIMP RISOTTO (diver scallops, shrimp, white truffle oil). She had the BEST meal at the table. risotto was cooked to perfection and the scallops were cooked perfectly. The dish was seasoned very well and there was plenty to share.  Another friend had the SUNDAY GRAVY (pork belly, meatballs, sausage tomato sauce, ricotta, penne). This was DEFINITELY the heaviest of the dishes, but soooo good and tasty. The meatballs were amazing.  I had TORTELLONI MIGNON (tenderloin, tomato cream sauce). It was tortelloni stuffed with seasoned filet mignon. Tasty with an amazing cream sauce.  I would DEFINITELY give this place another visit to try their other dishes. One of the best meals I've had at a restaurant in a LONG TIME.
Lovely place to celebrate an occasion. Staff is sweet and the neighborhood is nice.
Good Italian style  very nice Location
The downstairs bar is perfection and so chill. Great drinks and people.
Really great atmosphere and delicious food.
Little gem great food
Quaint

If you're looking for a  a cozy and intimate Italian dinner experience, Floriana is a destination to visit. It's almost like you're (literally) in the home of a loving relative, with the warmth you get at an extended family gathering. The wait staff is attentive and friendly, inviting you to try the specialties that will comfort or give the option to try something new. For the appetizer we shared the Black Gnocchi, a wonderful lobster and shrimp dish. For dinner, I had the tortellini mignon and it was amazing! I suggest being open to exploring dishes and sharing, as there are so many options. If you're up for it, pair the meals with a bottle of wine (a great value over glasses of wine), and you'll be set!
My favorite italian place in DC

I don't like to give one star because people discount the review but it was the worst dining experience I've had in DC, and I live here. Microwaved dishes came out part hot and partly cold-COME ON! Who does this? Returned plates came back the same way, only slightly hotter but still a cold center. Wine was too warm, pretty much nothing was right, can't believe they have a business.
The food is fantastic, the bread with pesto is a great start.

A true gem - authentic Italian restaurant tucked away in a quaint row home. So glad our friends took us here and finally discovered it! The cozy restaurant is bursting with flavor and reminiscent of the Osterias in Italy.  I love how the complementary Tuscan bread comes with olive oil and basil - true pesto. We enjoyed the bread basket, not a crumb was spared.  The creamy Burrata with sweet potato puree was divine and paired well with the bread. The plump burrata was so soft and juicy that it melted in my mouth. Hands down the best burrata I've had!  The Butternut Squash was another crowd-pleaser. The squash was well seasoned and the goat cheese and greens added nice flavor.  The tender Burrata Ravioli with juicy mushrooms smothered in creamy pesto sauce was delicious! The al dente ravioli with creamy cheese filling, tender mushrooms, and basil white sauce blended well together with lots of flavor. Every piece was delightfully devoured leaving a nice clean plate. My guy friends all thoroughly enjoyed their hearty meat pasta dishes as their plates were also left clean.  The Tiramisu was tasty, but not a stand-out. We were all stuffed from the bread, apps, and entrees that we didn't save room for dessert. I would skip the tiramisu and go for the Chocolate Bomba next time.  The 1/2 price bottle of wine and Wed and Sundays is a steal! We got a delicious bottle of Chianti Classico for $26 (normally $52). The service is attentive and polite.  One weird thing to note - the bathroom is on the 2nd floor, above the restaurant. Go upstairs, not downstairs! There's a little bar downstairs in the basement by the same owners but not part of the restaurant (different menus and drinks). I wondered downstairs before climbing up a couple flights of stairs to the restroom - getting those steps in!  Definitely make a reservation a week or so in advance. There's only a handful of tables and seating for like 25 people. We were lucky and got a reservation on Super Bowl Sunday a few days in advance (didn't want to painfully watch the underdogs team get defeated by the Pats). Glad we made the right choice to enjoy some fine Italian dining instead!  Can't wait to be back for some creamy Burrata and scrumptious Burrata Ravioli!

Romantic atmosphere, friendly staff, and the food was delicious. Sunday Gravy entree had a little bit of everything in it, pork belly, sausage, meatball, and pasta with a red sauce. Would go back again next time I am in DC.
Always the best. Service is impeccable and food is always special.
Food was just okay. Great homemade pesto though made with almonds. Won't be going back.

The food at Floriana is very tasty! Some very rustic pasta dishes, and the pasta is all cooked al dente. I do think the prices are a bit expensive, but the food is worth a try! The service was good during my meal and I will visit again.
(Translated by Google) Very good  (Original) Muy vueno

Best Italian place in all of dc!! It is a small place but i went there with my family of 8 and we all fit and were comfortable!  The pasta is all homemade and amazing! I had the burrata stuffed ravioli which was 10/10! I also started with some clam or mussels dish which was excellent as well. The menu is big for such a small place but not too big where it’s over-whelming. Everyone of us enjoyed our meals and we are not all the most simple eaters!  It is expensive but not for the portions! Good for a romantic evening or special occasion family dinners.  HIGHLY recommend. I work at a hotel and recommend this to guests all the time when I can. Amazing.

We had an excellent meal, mussels were delicious, homemade pasta with bolognese sauce and the rockfish were both fabulous and dessert was amazing- overall, excellent food and price(ask about prefix this week for restaurant week). Delicious desserts - homemade tiramisu and choc mousse were a perfect ending to my birthday dinner.

This was some of the finest food I’ve ever had so far in my life. My girlfriend and I had date here tonight and we enjoyed ourselves the entire time. The outside of the restaurant is nothing compared to the interior. The atmosphere of the decor was elegant with the paintings hung around the room and the dim lighting with the red walls. The waiters and waitresses were polite and attentive, and of course the food was incredible. I wish I could remember the names of everything I had eaten there. My appetizer had a pesto that was sweet in a way I never tasted before. My salad was a simple and delicious fresh baby greens with a sherry vinaigrette. The pasta I ate contained duck in a special sauce which is absolutely something I think everyone should try at least once, it was the highlight of my meal, even eating it with bread alone was delicious, And finally for dessert I ate the blueberry lemon pound cake with an Italian coffee. My closest complaint would be that I couldn’t taste the lavender cream in the cake, however my taste buds love sweets stronger than most, so I believe for everyone whose not like me would enjoy this cake and taste the lavender cream within it.  Take my word, eating here will make your night.

Excellent all around. Delicious, homemade Italian food - we had the lasagna, which is the only thing that's been on the menu since the restaurant opened and it was delicious, as well as the scallops which were perfectly seared and seasoned. Sunday night wine bottles are half price!  Atmosphere is very nice, easy to have conversations, and the staff were so friendly and prompt. We enjoyed dining here and will definitely be back!
Excellent ambiance in a cozy house in Dupont and the food is incredible. Highly recommend the boar pasta.

I was here for a friend's birthday brunch. Food was good - especially the biscuits! The server was great with answering questions and finding out answers to dietary concerns (no lard in the biscuits!- yay!). We were seated on the second floor, which was cozy with a nice view outside.

A small intimate dining setting perfect for a couple or small group. The food was tasty and the servers were all very kind. Only downside is the first floor can be a little cramped if you're a bigger person. My parter got the lasagna and I got the Shrimp and Scallop risotto. I very much prefered the lasagna but the scallops were absolutely phenomenal. Unfortunately it was only 2 scallops and 3 shrimp. Dessert was underwhelming but we had a great time nonetheless. Perfect restaurant for anniversaries or for a celebratory dinner.
Great food and company in intimate setting. The service is exceptional and the lunch combinations are great. I recommend the beet salad and sweet potato with duck gnocchi.

I've been looking to check out Floriana for a while now, and they didn't disappoint.  High ceilings and somewhat of an intimate seating arrangement, it's hard not to hear the loud acoustics of the entire restaurant. However, I felt that those two things added personality to the place.  Each table to the side of us had raved about the brussels sprout appetizer, so we tried that along with the fried calamari. Both were outstanding. This gave me a really good feeling about the lamb gnoochi, along with shrimp & scallop entrees. Not only were they delicious, but I think I was even more impressed with the proportions. Often, with restaurants who focus on presentation, either the quantity or quality suffer. Not here. Overall... I'd highly recommend this place and have plans on returning as soon as possible.
Neighborhood spot with delicious food and a great wine selection. Be sure to check out Dito’s bar in the English basement before or after your meal.

Had the pleasure of dining there last Wednesday evening.  The meal was incredible as was the service.  The chef is friendly and very knowledgeable.  The bar puts out a top notch old fashioned and it is a fun place to hang out.  Thanks for a great experience, cant wait to visit again in March.
Amazing space for a date night or to gather with friends. And the food is consistently good
Went for a food pick up ,the food did look good
Very good food, unconventional space in an old Victorian. Good vibes only, gay friendly, nay, encouraged.
Nice
Fantastic. Food and service is excellent. The arancini was light and delicious. The burrata ravioli was excellent. We'll be back.

On our first visit, I had the lamb gnocchi and my husband had the Sunday gravy, which is basically all the meats plus short penne. Both were to die for. On the second visit, which happened to be my birthday, we split the arancini, bibb salad, lasagna, and duck breast on top of chard and sweet potato gnocchi. All were heavenly. 😋 For dessert, we split tiramisu, which when compared to the stellar apps and mains, was average.  We were directed here by a woman sitting next to us at Hank's Oyster Bar. Floriana is great for a special date or a casual walk-in.

Ambiance: a super cute, romantically dim lit scene with mostly couples occupying the dining room.  Service: absolutely wonderful.  All staff members always made sure guests were well taken care of. While we were waiting for our table to get ready, every staff member walking by the host stand made sure we were already being helped.  Drinks:  Standard selection of cocktails and wine/champagne menus. The sangria was ok. The high tea was delicious.  Food: this is where I was a bit disappointed. After hearing that lasagna was their most popular dish, I decided to try it. It was mediocre. The cheese layer was crispy and delicious, but it just did not live up to the hype. The shrimp risotto was delicious though. We were offered complimentary dessert to celebrate our anniversary though which was very sweet.
Excellent food and excellent staff. Snobby customers. Grow up people. Allow others to eat their food the way they want. Staff was very nice and the gnocchi with squid ink was amazing.
-    I asked for a ravioli that came cold and with no flavor at all.. My friend ordered a meat that was not in the temperature that he asked and even more flavorless. +   Drinks were fantastic

Went there on a Tuesday night. Service was amazing - they got our orders wrong and the server was able to replace it very quickly. On top of that, they gave us complementary dessert to make up for it. However, the food was smothered in grease and did not taste very good. They also do not know how to cook their lamb. But gnocchi texture was excellent. Their services is the only redeeming quality for the food.

We were there for restaurant week and had a lovely meal - highly suggest their Beaujolais wine, lobster gnocchi appetizer,  duck breast and the lamb gnocchi! The espresso and chocolate mousse dessert was the best!

The food is good,  but my favorite part about this place is by far the bar downstairs. It is small, cosy, and friendly. They have a small-ish selection of great wines (you won't need more options). The bartender has always been generous with the pours, and willing to make whatever drinks we ask for (on the menu, or not). I've never not stumbled out of this place feeling glad we came back.
This is a real italian restaurant. I had fried calamari and pappardelle with wild boar sauce, paired with a glass of Nebbiolo. Everything was excellent!
Pre theater dinner. The cocktails are refreshing, we had a light dinner of salads and muscles and they were delicious. The staff are enjoyable to talk to and make the whole meal a nice experience.

Great little place for dinner.  Make a reservation or come early to get a spot in the full service bar downstairs.  Pasta dishes are well executed and hearty, like an upgraded version of what my Italian friends and family make for special occasions.  They have a good wine list that's heavily influenced by Italy w some good French and California wines too.
Atmosphere was great.  Food was amazing.  Service was on par.  No complaints - will be back!
Great science experience the for brunch. Gnocchi and eggs benedict were great. Service was excellent also.
Had the Lamb gnocchi. Its was great. Half off bottles of wine on Wednesday!

This is not one of the places any of the guides told us about but it was by far the best dinner we had here. Off the beaten path and nothing that jumps out at you from the outside but inside is very different. From the homemade parsley spread for the bread to the delish entrees and the wonderful desserts it was a very enjoyable meal.
Wonderful food as always.
Delicious food, seating is tight, still gets 5 stars
Food is just ok, but their pesto is super good!

Used to be amazing but the service has gone downhill and the food was nowhere near as good as it used to be. The duck was burnt and the gnocchi that used to be incredible tasted pretty average. Such a shame!

Oh my food was fabulous - lasagna so homemade taste - really rich flavors - ask for Matthew he didn’t miss a beat on great service - very professional !!!!  Won’t be disappointed if you are lucky enough to get a table !!
Excellent lasagna and chocolate mousse.

We went on a nice night so we ate outside! It was lively in the outside area with a great vibe! My girlfriend and I went on a Wednesday and there was a special for half priced wine bottles! We had to get one went with a lovely red. For appetizer we started with a cheese board with a quality brie and some forme di formaggio paired with salumi, and olives! All was great! For our main course I got gnocchi with lamb which was pretty good but lacking in flavor. The lamb I will say was really good but again lacking in flavor but perfect texture! My girlfriend got the lasagna which didn't disappoint! We were really full after so there wasn't any room for desert. Overall great experience...but I will say I noticed I was the only non-white person, wasn't a big deal but something I noticed.  With that said I'd still go back because it was a good experience with great service a menu waiting to be explored!
Better than Filomena! Can't believe it

Food tasted terrible but the service was even worse.  I didn’t leave a tip it was so bad.  They took it off the bill but didn’t bother asking when it could have made a difference.  The table they sat us at was 10 degrees hotter than the rest of the tables. We sweat the entire time.  On a side note the calamari was really good, but it does not make up for the rest.
Went for wine and apps, both good, very good service
Very cute place,  good ambience, great food,  excellent service.
Best Italian near Dupont!
Quiet and cozy spot with great food
Outstanding dinner with my wifes cousins.
The food and ambiance is good , but what makes it stand out, are the staff. They're nothing short of incredible. Keep it up everyone.
Very charming restaurant and outdoor seating area is very nice for a sunny afternoon. Food is also great.
One of our favorite places to eat. All four of us had excellent food and outstanding service. Need to go more often.
Love it always!  Never disappoints!
I've been a couple of times and the service is often hit or miss, but the food is more often pretty solid.

We called in an order to feed 30 people all visiting for a funeral. Knowing it was a slim chance any restaurant could accommodate such a large order in same day notice, we called several hours in advance. Floriana didn't blink an eye, and said they'd make it happen for us. Not only did we get everything we ordered in the time we needed, but it was also hot and amazingly delicious. Everyone raved at the quality of the lasagna, gnocchi, ravioli, fried chicken, salad and sides. Everyone knows food is the one thing that can help mend a broken heart in tragic times, and we thank the people at Floriana for providing all of hearts comfort with their gorgeous Italian cuisine.
Very cool!

When searching for Italian food in DC this will or should be at the top of your list. A small restaurant but full of flavor. My wife and I made reservations here for a nice dinner to celebrate our anniversary. The staff very friendly and knowledgeable on the menu with strong recommendations. We ordered the calamari to start, but wasn't as pleased there, a little too salty for my taste. On to the main courses, she ordered the shrimp & scallop risotto that was AMAZING, highly recommend. I ordered the beef tenderloin ravioli that also very flavorful and made up for the calamari!  Being we were celebrating, we also at the tiramisu, very nice.
Fabulous lasagna
Brunch was excellent, and the bottomless mimosas were some of the best I've ever had.

The setting of the restaurant makes you feel as if you were at home. Built inside a townhome, gives you the feel of a very intimate setting.  The service exceeded expectations! We had our appetizers, and drink orders within 10 minutes of being seated.  Food was excellent, and incredibly fresh, and we'll portioned. Rich in taste, and perfectly seasoned.

My wife went here for our first anniversary while visiting DC. The whole experience was fantastic. Our waiter was extremely friendly and the owner came out to talk to everyone as well. The decor inside was very quaint and made a great unique experience. The food was amazing as well. I had the lamb gnocchi and my wife had the seafood risotto. I would definitely recommend to anyone in the DC area and I would go back.
Homemade pasta and cheese.
Great neighborhood spot for Italian.
food was good!  make sure to have a reservation!  the bar area downstairs is cramped and loud
Superb Italian cuisine, excellent ambiance, above average service.

I went here for my birthday with my boyfriend. We had a phenomenal time. We made reservations and I believe it was helpful since we were seated immediately. The wait staff was very polite but weren’t very personable. However, that wasn’t much of a hindrance because we enjoyed the intimate space. Overall, I had a great experience and enjoyed how accommodating they were for my special day. Will definitely visit again.
Oh my, I ate the whole thing!!! Food and service was the best I've had in a long time. Thanks
The arancini and dessert is very good The entree is mediocre compared to arancini and dessert.

(Translated by Google) I think it's one of the great Italian restaurants in Washington DC. Since it is a single house, it is by no means large, but the staff's awareness was thorough, and a person who was aware as an owner or manager was also around each table. The photo menus are in order CAPRESE, CALAMARI FRITTI, BURRATA, FREED BRUSSELS SPROUTS, SCALLOP & SHRIMP RISOTTO, RAVIOLI DI ZUCCA However, all were very satisfied. Pasta must be delicious, but this time I was full and I couldn't eat it. Thank you for the delicious food.  (Original) Washington DCの素晴らしいイタリアンのひとつだと思う。 一軒家を使っているので、決して広くはないが、staffの気づかいは行き届き、更にowner若しくはmanagerと覚しき人物も各テーブルを回っていた。 写真のmenuは順に CAPRESE、CALAMARI FRITTI、BURRATA、FRIED BRUSSELS SPROUTS、SCALLOP & SHRIMP RISOTTO、RAVIOLI DI ZUCCA だったが、何れも大満足だった。 パスタも美味しいに違いないが、今回は満腹で食べられなかった。 美味しい料理をありがとう。

Excellent food, delicious wine, top notch service. The caprese (which includes house made fresh mozzarella), risotto, and the duck carbonara were all delicious - I think the vegetarian risotto was the best. Our waiter made a very good wine pairing selection, and the meal was overall wonderful. We had tiramasu and espresso chocolate mousse for desert, both delicious. The mousse was on the firmer side, yet melted in your mouth.  I mentioned top notch service. The waitstaff were courteous and efficient, if course, but the teamwork really impressed me. I was finishing a plate and someone who was neither a waiter or bussing staff (manager, I think) took the empty plate with no disruption at all. That really  speaks to great service and making the guests comfortable.  Finally, the ambiance was  beautifully romantic. It's an old town house with barely any changes, so you feel like you're eating a cozy dining room. I think our table was in what used to be the living room, and had nice false fireplace to boot.
Authentic terrific tasting food!
By far one of the best restaurants I have ever eaten at! I highly recommend, everything from the food to the mixed drinks was amazing!
Great food, nice atmosphere. Crowded, and they forgot the bread.
The entire evening was fabulous from the food to the atmosphere and service. This is a must-see in Washington DC.
Great evening out with my wife, food was top notch and the wait staff was excellent. Thank you
Excellent food and service at good price. My modest reservation was that the bread with the Benedict was a little tough but otherwise, Great overall.
Tortellini mignon was awesome. Very nice place. Service was good also
Food was delicious and staff was very friendly. The owner also came by to make sure we enjoyed everything.
Always a great meal.
Excellent service, wonderful food, a lovely evening. Fried brussel sprouts and lasagna was marvelous. Highly recommend this intimate, well-priced, little gem.
Meal would have been much better if the heat was not added in. Too much chili/hot pepper added in.
Sat outdoors.  Great food.
(Translated by Google) Delocious everything. I recommend it  (Original) Delocioso todo. Lo recomiendo
Lovely good, ambience and service! Very cosy too!
Overpriced food. They also didn't have any of thy desserts I wanted. Only reason why I'm giving 2 stars and not 1 is because the waitress was nice
Small dining room, great service.

Incredible! Went with my daughter on a Monday night. Busy yet we did not wait even though we neglected to make a reservation. We both ordered the Sunday gravy and it was the BEST pasta I had ever eaten. Sauce tastes like they have an old lady straight from Sicily in the kitchen! Short rib, meatballs and Italian sausage simmered in gravy. Service was awesome! My daughter is only ten and I have come to expect not so great service in trendier upscale restaurants when you walk in with a child but this was definitely not the case here. Prompt service timed perfectly. We will definitely be back!
Italian restaurant in middle of dc
The food is excellent. Lasagna and the ravioli  were great. Service was terrific, we love the decor and the look of the restaurant in the charming townhouse. The space has a romantic flair.

This is a hidden gem.  It looks like a row house from the outside. There is not a lot of seating, so you see want to make a reservation. Food was great, and they did a special food pricing so we got three dishes for 35 bucks.
We loved everything we got, including dessert :) Highly recommend!
An amazing evening with wonderful combinations of taste and service! We would come back often if we lived close!!

Celebrated my birthday at this beautiful restaurant. The wait staff and the manager were  incredibly nice and attentive. The food was excellent and my birthday dessert was amazing. This is by far one of the best Italian restaurants! I strongly suggest Floriana as a great restaurant for any occasion!
The restaurant is in an old converted house. The food is very delicious. The portions are generous. The staff is very attentive and friendly.

Had walked pasted here several times, so we decided to try it. What a great decision that was. The owner greeted us at the door, we were immediately seated, service was prompt. Wine selection was great. But the real treat was the food, WOW! There is a reason they have been in business for over 40 years and a few of the dishes still have the same receipe for all those years. I had the SHORT RIB AGNOLOTTI and it was delightful. Treat your tastebuds!
Very good Italian restaurant. Fancy and traditional Italian dishes. The tiramisu is fantastic!

Food allergy guru!  The owner came to the table to make absolutely sure exactly what was safe and explain the procedures they wld be taking to assure safety.  Plus the food was so good.  My grilled salmon was perfect.
Favorite DC Italian spot. Cozy, warm, intimate.
Very good. Best calamari I've had I  a while. Perfectly cooked. A bit loud for casual conversation. But overall a good fate night location.
Good service, good food, great atmosphere, especially for dates! Try them on Monday and Tuesday nights and get three courses for $35, or half-price wine bottles on Wednesdays and Sundays.
Great food, service, wine and a cozy atmosphere.

My husband and I dined here during restaurant week so it was quite packed. Everything from the hostess and serving staff to the food and drinks were tremendous. The complementary pesto spread and fresh bread sold us from the beginning. Best Italian food in D.C.
Brilliant Italian food in a charming dining room at a modest price. Worth a trip.
Wow.  This place is just incredible.  Some of the best italian food I've ever had the pleasure of eating.  I will go back first thing the next time I'm in DC.
Floriana has the best Italian food I have ever eaten in my entire life. Everything was done fast and was so good! Will definitely recommend this place to anyone and everyone. I will certainly return.
Best Italian restaurant in DC!
Love this place. Seriously excellent Italian food. I loved everything I had. Very good service too and totally fair pricing. I 100% recommend trying this place out.
The food is amazing. Warm and cozy, perfect for dates. Attentive staff who won't rush you. Don't skip dessert!
Fantastic, food, staff and ambiance...can't say enough wonderful things!
Excellent duck. Knowledgeable and attentive waitstaff.

Exceptional Italian fare.  Service is excellent, and prices are reasonable.  Only complaint is that seating can be tight, since the place is so very busy.  Make sure you make reservations ahead of time.  Well worth it.  Been many times, and never had a bad meal.
Great food deals on Monday's and Tuesday's:$35 for an appetizer/salad, entree, and dessert. Also, the outside patio was lovely
Best food I've had around Dupont Circle so far.  My parents used to live in this house when I was a baby..
Lovely Italian food and great wine list.
Wonderful food, friendly wait staff.
